  "local_port": 42244,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I link my valid Aadhaar card to the SBI?",
  "response": "Linking your Aadhaar card to your State Bank of India (SBI) account can be done through several methods. Here are the steps for each method:\n\n### 1. **Using Online Banking:**\n   - **Log in** to your SBI online banking account.\n   - Navigate to the **'Profile'** tab.\n   - Click on **'Link Aadhaar'**.\n   - Enter your Aadhaar number and submit.\n   - You may receive a confirmation message once the linking is successful.\n\n### 2. **Using the SBI Mobile App:**\n   - Open the **SBI YONO App** on your mobile device.\n   - Log in to your account.\n   - Go to the **'Services'** section.\n   - Select **'Link Aadhaar'**.\n   - Enter your Aadhaar number and submit.\n   - Wait for the confirmation message.\n\n### 3. **Via SMS:**\n   - You can also link your Aadhaar by sending an SMS.\n   - Type the message in the following format:  \n     `UID <Aadhaar Number> <Account Number>`  \n   - Send it to **567676** or **9223566666**.\n\n### 4. **Visiting the Bank Branch:**\n   - Visit your nearest SBI branch.\n   - Carry your Aadhaar card and a copy of it.\n   - Fill out the Aadhaar linking form available at the branch.\n   - Submit the form along with your Aadhaar copy to the bank official.\n   - You will receive a confirmation once the linking is done.\n\n### 5. **Using ATM:**\n   - Visit an SBI ATM.\n   - Insert your debit card and enter your PIN.\n   - Select the option for **'Aadhaar Linking'**.\n   - Follow the prompts to complete the linking process.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- Make sure your Aadhaar details are correct and updated, as discrepancies can cause issues during the linking process.\n- It\u2019s advisable to keep your mobile number linked to your Aadhaar active, as you may receive OTPs or confirmation messages related to the linking process.\n\nIf you face any issues, you can contact SBI customer service for assistance.",
